    explanation: "Under the tax benefit rule (IRC §111), a state tax refund is included in income to the extent the prior deduction provided a tax benefit. The taxpayer deducted $10,000 (SALT cap) and received a $10,000 refund. Since the full $10,000 deduction provided a benefit (reduced taxable income), the entire $10,000 refund is includible. If the taxpayer had taken the standard deduction instead, no portion would be taxable.",
