    educational: "The tax benefit rule prevents taxpayers from getting a double benefit. If a deduction reduces your taxable income in one year, and you later recover some of that deduction, the recovered amount is generally included in your income in the year it's received, but only to the extent you benefited from the deduction in the first place. This ensures that you're only taxed on your true economic income over time.",
    examTip: "Always consider the SALT limitation when calculating the taxable portion of a state income tax refund; the taxable amount is capped by the actual deduction taken, not the original amount paid.",
