    educational: "The §754 election allows a partnership to adjust the inside basis of its assets to reflect changes in the outside basis of the partners' interests. This prevents distortions when a partner's interest is transferred or when distributions cause gain or loss recognition, ensuring a fairer allocation of income and deductions among the partners.",
    examTip: "Remember that §734(b) adjustments are all about maintaining parity between the inside and outside basis; focus on distributions causing gain/loss or basis discrepancies.",
    memoryAid: "734(b) = Basis Bump (or Bust) after Distributions",
    reference: "IRC §734(b); §754; §755",
