    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Above-the-line deductions (FOR AGI — IRC §62): reduce gross income to arrive at AGI. Key deductions FOR AGI: (1) 50% of self-employment tax, (2) Self-employed health insurance (100%), (3) IRA contributions (traditional, if deductible), (4) Student loan interest (up to $2,500), (5) HSA contributions, (6) Alimony paid (pre-2019 divorces only), (7) Educator expenses ($300), (8) Moving expenses (military only post-TCJA), (9) Business expenses (Schedule C/F), (10) Losses from sale of property. Below-the-line (FROM AGI): standard deduction or itemized deductions (medical > 7.5% AGI, SALT up to $10K, mortgage interest, charitable, casualty from federally declared disasters). AGI is the critical threshold for many phase-outs.",
