      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - One-half of self-employment tax is a deduction FOR AGI, meaning it's deducted directly from gross income to arrive at adjusted gross income (AGI). This deduction reflects the employer portion of social security and Medicare taxes that self-employed individuals must pay.",
