    explanation: "IRC §643(a) / §651 / §661: DNI = the trust/estate's taxable income, modified by: (1) adding back the distribution deduction, (2) adding tax-exempt interest (net of allocable expenses), (3) excluding capital gains allocable to corpus. Purpose: (1) Limits the trust/estate's distribution deduction (the entity deducts the lesser of distributions or DNI). (2) Limits the amount taxable to beneficiaries (beneficiaries include the lesser of distributions received or their proportionate share of DNI). Character of income passes through to beneficiaries proportionally (the \"tier system\" for complex trusts). Simple trusts: must distribute all income currently, no charitable deduction, no corpus distributions. Complex trusts: may accumulate income, may make charitable contributions from income, may distribute corpus.",
