      2: "Why option C is WRONG - The trustee's fee is an expense that *affects* the calculation of taxable income, which is a component of DNI, but it is not the definition of DNI itself. Trustee fees are generally deductible expenses.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - DNI does not dictate the *minimum* amount a trust must distribute; the trust document itself governs distribution requirements. DNI merely limits the tax consequences of distributions that *are* made.",
