    explanation: "IRC §1031 — Boot in like-kind exchanges: Boot = cash received + FMV of non-like-kind property received + net debt relief (liabilities assumed by the other party exceeding liabilities the taxpayer assumes). Gain recognized = the lesser of (1) boot received, or (2) realized gain. Losses are NEVER recognized in a §1031 exchange (even with boot). Basis of property received: basis of property given up + gain recognized − boot received (simplified). Mortgage netting: if taxpayer is relieved of a $100K mortgage but takes on a $60K mortgage, net boot = $40K (debt relief). Boot given (cash paid) reduces gain recognition. Post-TCJA (2018+): §1031 applies ONLY to real property (personal property exchanges no longer qualify). Must identify replacement property within 45 days, close within 180 days.",
