    explanation: "IRC §1223 (Holding Period Tacking): The holding period of the relinquished property tacks onto the replacement property when the basis carries over or is determined by reference to the old property. Applies to: §1031 exchanges, §1033 involuntary conversions, §351 transfers (transferor's holding period tacks for transferred asset), gifts (donor's holding period tacks for FMV basis), §721 transfers to a partnership. Does NOT tack: inherited property (always treated as long-term — §1223(9)), purchased property, boot property received in an exchange (holding period starts from exchange date). Boot property (non-like-kind): new holding period begins on the date of the exchange. For partial carryover/partial FMV basis situations: split the holding period accordingly.",
