    correctAnswer: 2,
    explanation: "IRC §165(h) (post-TCJA): Personal casualty/theft losses: deductible ONLY if attributable to a federally declared disaster (FEMA declaration). Calculation: (1) Loss per event = lesser of decrease in FMV or adjusted basis − insurance recovery. (2) Subtract $100 per casualty event. (3) Subtract 10% of AGI from the aggregate net casualty loss. Exception: personal casualty gains exist → can net gains and losses regardless of disaster status. Business/rental casualty losses: still fully deductible (no TCJA limitation). Pre-TCJA (and post-2025 if TCJA sunsets): all personal casualties deductible with the $100/10% floors. The disaster must be declared by the President under the Stafford Act. Theft losses: include fraud (Ponzi scheme losses get special treatment under Rev. Proc. 2009-20).",
