      2: "Why option C is CORRECT - The Tax Cuts and Jobs Act (TCJA) significantly limited the deductibility of personal casualty losses. Now, only losses attributable to a federally declared disaster are deductible, and these are subject to both a $100-per-event floor and a 10%-of-AGI floor.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - While there is a $100 floor, the main reason this is incorrect is that only losses from federally declared disasters are deductible, not just any loss over $100.",
