    explanation: "IRC §1377(a): S corporation: pro rata allocation. Each shareholder's share = (shares owned on each day ÷ total shares outstanding on each day) × the S corp's income/loss/deduction items for the year. No special allocations: unlike partnerships, S corps cannot allocate items disproportionately (all items are allocated per-share, per-day). If a shareholder's interest terminates during the year: (1) Default: per-share/per-day for the full year. (2) Election: all affected shareholders can elect to close the books as of the termination date (§1377(a)(2)) — treats the year as two short periods. Items pass through maintaining their character: capital gains, §1231 gains, charitable contributions, tax-exempt income, etc. Each shareholder reports their share on Form 1040 (from Schedule K-1).",
