    explanation: "IRC §280A (Vacation Home Rules — three categories): (1) De minimis rental (< 15 rental days): rental income is excluded from gross income. No rental expenses deductible (except mortgage interest/taxes as itemized deductions). (2) Primarily rental (personal use ≤ greater of 14 days or 10% of rental days): treated as rental property. Rental losses are deductible (subject to passive activity rules). Expenses allocated based on rental days/total days. (3) Personal/rental use (≥ 15 rental days AND personal use > greater of 14 days or 10% of rental days): rental income reported. Expenses allocated between personal and rental. Rental deductions limited to rental income (NO net loss). Ordering of deductions: (a) Interest/taxes (allocated portion), (b) Operating expenses, (c) Depreciation — each tier deductible only to the extent of remaining rental income. Excess carries forward.",
