      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Tax Court opinions are judicial interpretations of the tax law, but they are subordinate to the IRC and are binding only on the specific taxpayer and within the jurisdiction of the Tax Court, unless affirmed by a higher court.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - IRS Revenue Rulings represent the IRS's interpretation of the tax law applied to specific factual situations; while they provide guidance, they are subordinate to the IRC and Treasury Regulations.",
