    explanation: "IRC §401(a)(9) (RMD Rules — post-SECURE 2.0): RMD beginning age: Born before 1951: 70½. Born 1951-1959: 73 (SECURE 2.0, effective 2023). Born 1960+: 75 (effective 2033). First RMD deadline: April 1 of the year following the year the individual reaches the applicable age (but then must also take the second RMD by 12/31 of that same year → potential double distribution). Penalty for missed RMD: 25% of the shortfall (reduced from 50% by SECURE 2.0). Further reduced to 10% if corrected within 2 years. RMD calculation: account balance (12/31 of prior year) ÷ life expectancy factor (Uniform Lifetime Table, or Joint and Last Survivor Table if sole beneficiary is spouse > 10 years younger). Roth IRAs: NO RMDs during owner's lifetime. Inherited IRAs: 10-year rule for most non-spouse beneficiaries (SECURE Act).",
