      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Net worth (assets minus liabilities) is a balance sheet concept reflecting a company's overall financial position, whereas E&P is more focused on the company's ability to pay dividends.",
      3: "Why option D is CORRECT - Current E&P, along with accumulated E&P, dictates whether a distribution to shareholders is treated as a taxable dividend. Distributions are considered dividends to the extent of E&P; amounts exceeding E&P are treated as a return of capital (reducing basis) and then as capital gain.",
