    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "IRC §408(d)(8) (QCD): Age requirement: 70½ or older (not 73 — QCD age was NOT increased when RMD age changed). Annual limit: $105,000 (2025, indexed — SECURE 2.0 provides for inflation adjustment starting 2024). Must be: (1) Direct transfer from IRA (traditional or Roth) to a qualified charity (§501(c)(3)). (2) Not a donor-advised fund, supporting organization, or private foundation. (3) Would be deductible as a charitable contribution (if not from IRA). Benefits: (1) Excluded from gross income (not just deducted — better than deducting because it doesn't increase AGI). (2) Counts toward RMD. (3) Beneficial for taxpayers who take the standard deduction (get charitable benefit without itemizing). (4) Doesn't affect MAGI-based phaseouts (Social Security taxability, Medicare premiums, etc.). SECURE 2.0 addition: one-time QCD of up to $53,000 to a charitable remainder trust or charitable gift annuity.",
