    educational: "The 'hot asset' rules exist to prevent partners from using the sale of their partnership interest to convert what would otherwise be ordinary income (like accounts receivable or inventory profits) into more favorably taxed capital gains. This ensures that income is taxed according to its underlying nature, regardless of how it's realized.",
    examTip: "Remember the acronym 'URI' (Unrealized Receivables and Inventory) to quickly identify hot assets on the exam.",
    memoryAid: "Think of 'Hot Assets' as 'Ordinary' because they generate ordinary income when sold.",
    reference: "IRC §751",
