    explanation: "Trust and estate income tax rates (2024): 10% on taxable income up to $3,100; 24% on $3,100-$11,150; 35% on $11,150-$15,200; 37% on taxable income over $15,200. Note: the threshold for the 37% bracket adjusts annually for inflation (approximately $14,450 for 2024). These are the most compressed brackets in the federal tax system — for comparison, individual taxpayers reach 37% at approximately $609,350 (single) or $731,200 (MFJ). This compression creates a strong incentive to: (1) distribute income to beneficiaries in lower brackets (income distribution deduction reduces trust taxable income), (2) time distributions strategically, (3) consider grantor trust treatment where the grantor pays tax at their individual rates. Trusts and estates also pay the 3.8% Net Investment Income Tax (NIIT) on the lesser of: undistributed net investment income or AGI exceeding the threshold ($14,450 for 2024 — same as the 37% bracket). This makes trusts potentially subject to a combined rate of 40.8% (37% + 3.8%) at relatively low income levels.",
