    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "IRC §541-§547 Personal Holding Company (PHC) Tax: Two-test classification: (1) Stock ownership test (§542(a)(2)): more than 50% of the value of outstanding stock is owned (directly or constructively under §544) by 5 or fewer individuals at any time during the last half of the tax year. Constructive ownership: family attribution, entity attribution, option attribution. (2) Income test (§542(a)(1)): at least 60% of adjusted ordinary gross income (AOGI) is PHC income — includes: dividends, interest, royalties (unless 50%+ of OGI), rent (unless 50%+ of AOGI and PHC income does not exceed 10% of OGI after rent adjustments), annuities, personal service contracts where someone can designate who performs services. Excludes: tax-exempt corporations, lending companies, certain foreign corporations, S corporations (not subject to PHC tax). PHC tax: 20% of undistributed PHC income. Undistributed PHC income = taxable income minus: federal income taxes, net capital gain (minus taxes thereon), dividends paid (including consent dividends and throwback dividends). Remedy: paying sufficient dividends eliminates the PHC tax.",
