    examTip: "When evaluating a corporation for PHC status, always check the stock ownership first, then calculate the adjusted ordinary gross income and PHC income to see if both tests are met.",
    memoryAid: "Think of '5-60': 5 or fewer shareholders, 60% or more PHC income.",
    reference: "IRC §541-§547",
