    explanation: "IRC §1361 S Corporation eligibility requirements: (1) Domestic corporation, (2) Maximum 100 shareholders — family members (within 6 generations) may elect to be treated as a single shareholder under §1361(c)(1), (3) Eligible shareholders only — individuals, estates, certain trusts (grantor trusts, qualified subchapter S trusts (QSSTs), electing small business trusts (ESBTs)), tax-exempt organizations (§401(a) and §501(c)(3)). NOT eligible shareholders: partnerships, C corporations, nonresident aliens. (4) One class of stock — all outstanding shares must have identical rights to distribution and liquidation proceeds. Differences in voting rights are permitted (voting and nonvoting common stock OK). (5) Not an ineligible corporation — certain financial institutions, insurance companies, domestic international sales corporations (DISCs), and certain affiliated groups are ineligible. Election: Form 2553, filed by the 15th day of the 3rd month of the tax year (or at any time during the preceding tax year). Must be signed by all shareholders.",
