    educational: "Corporations, unlike individuals, generally cannot rely on a prior year's tax liability to avoid underpayment penalties (except for the first installment for large corporations). They must estimate their current year's tax liability and pay it in quarterly installments to avoid penalties. This ensures the government receives tax revenue throughout the year.",
    examTip: "Pay close attention to the specific dollar amounts and due dates related to estimated tax payments for both individuals and corporations, as these are frequently tested.",
    memoryAid: "Think of 'C-Corp $500' to remember the threshold for C corporation estimated taxes.",
    reference: "IRC §6655",
