      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - The IRC §243 allows a 65% dividends received deduction when a corporation owns 20% to less than 80% of the distributing corporation's stock. This deduction mitigates the effects of triple taxation.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - An 80% dividends received deduction is not the correct percentage for ownership between 20% and 80%.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - A 100% dividends received deduction generally applies only to dividends received from members of an affiliated group (80% or more ownership).",
