    educational: "The dividends received deduction (DRD) is designed to alleviate the burden of triple taxation on corporate earnings. Without it, corporate profits could be taxed at the distributing corporation level, again when received as dividends by another corporation, and finally when distributed to individual shareholders. The percentage of the DRD depends on the ownership stake the receiving corporation has in the distributing corporation.",
    examTip: "Pay close attention to the ownership percentages when calculating the dividends received deduction; a seemingly small difference can significantly impact the allowable deduction.",
