    educational: "An Offer in Compromise (OIC) allows taxpayers to resolve their tax debt with the IRS for a lower amount than what they originally owed. There are three main grounds for an OIC: doubt as to collectibility (inability to pay), doubt as to liability (disagreement with the tax assessment), and effective tax administration (economic hardship or other compelling circumstances). Understanding the basis for the OIC is crucial for determining eligibility.",
