      1: "Option B is WRONG because while the §121 exclusion *might* apply partially, it doesn't eliminate the entire gain; the gain must be allocated between qualified (personal use) and nonqualified (rental) use periods, and the rental period is nonqualified.",
      2: "Option C is WRONG because the fair market value (FMV) at the time of conversion is only relevant for calculating a *loss* if the property is later sold at a loss; it doesn't automatically become the new basis for calculating a gain.",
