    question: "John and Mary are married, both age 52, and covered under a high-deductible health plan (HDHP) with a family deductible. In 2024, their HDHP has a deductible of $4,000. They want to maximize their health savings account (HSA) contributions. What is the maximum amount they can contribute to their HSA for 2024, assuming they are otherwise eligible?",
